    "title": "Can You Even?",
    "level": "A2",
    "pattern": {
        "title": "Energy verbs: jaksaa, ehtiä, viitsiä",
        "summary": "Three verbs Finns use constantly and textbooks barely teach: jaksaa = to have the energy, ehtiä = to have the time, viitsiä = to be bothered. Emmä jaksa = I'm too tired, mä en ehtiny = I didn't have time, emmä viitti = I can't be bothered.",
        "examples": [
            "Emmä jaksa enää. = I don't have the energy anymore.",
            "Ehitsä auttaa mua tänään? = Do you have time to help me today?",
            "Emmä viitti lähtee. = I can't be bothered to go."
        ]
    },
